0.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Horse --- **Description:** These can most often be found on plains. Their usefulness as transportation has made them valuable since ancient times. That said, wild horses do tend to get spooked and run off when approached, so if you're looking to snag one, it's best to sneak up on it. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Akkala Highlands

1.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Giant Horse --- **Description:** This giant horse is the last of its kind. Its physical capabilities completely overshadow those of regular horses, but its temperament is extremely wild. Only a truly skilled rider can train, or even catch, this beast of a mount. This is a horse that chooses its rider. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

2.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** White Horse --- **Description:** The Hyrulean royal family that perished over 100 years ago would sometimes ride atop white horses as a display of their divine right. This white horse may be a descendant of one once ridden by royalty. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

3.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Giant White Stallion --- **Description:** This massive animal is thought to share its lineage with the white horses ridden by Hylian royalty. Called a "giant white stallion" due to its color and enormous size. This horse is believed to have been the result of a sudden mutation. There are many travelers and researchers keen to seek out this extraordinary creature. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

4.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Golden Horse --- **Description:** An extremely rare horse with a golden coat, said to appear only once every hundred years. The horse's exquisite appearance belies a rugged constitution that makes it adaptable to harsh environments. Highly alert, and picky about who may ride it. Few riders could ever hope to tame this horse. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

5.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Stalhorse --- **Description:** A skeletal horse often ridden by monsters. These animals, which used to be ordinary horses, are said to be revived in areas where there is a high gloom concentration. They can only maintain their forms in darkness, and they have the remarkable ability to run atop gloom. --- **Common Locations:** Faron Grasslands, Hyrule Ridge

6.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Donkey --- **Description:** Smaller than horses, these are raised as livestock in the countryside, so they don't exist in the wild. They're more powerful than they look and specialize in transporting baggage. This has made them popular with traveling merchants. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule

7.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Sand Seal --- **Description:** These seals use their large flippers to move through the sand as if swimming. They were once wild animals but have since been domesticated by the Gerudo. They rely on their excellent hearing to find their way while submerged in the sand. Their large, distinct tusks look pretty ferocious, but their favorite food is actually fruit. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert

8.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Patricia --- **Description:** This is Riju's own sand seal. It may look intense, but she dotes on it regularly; the ribbon it wears was a gift from her, and it even has its own pen in Gerudo Town. It's far more agile than any other sand seal and far more outgoing. An ever-reliable partner to Riju, Patricia is always ready to take off through the desert at a moment's notice. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert

9.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Bushy-Tailed Squirrel --- **Description:** These small creatures are known for their large tails. They tend to live in forests and subsist on acorns and other nuts. They carry their food in their mouths but will sometimes drop it when surprised in an adorable display of shock. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Acorn --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Hyrule Ridge

10.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Woodland Boar --- **Description:** These medium-sized beasts can be found all throughout Hyrule. You can most often find them foraging for food in forests or meadows. Although usually docile, they won't hesitate to charge you full force if you get too close. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, West Necluda

11.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Red-Tusked Boar --- **Description:** These boars are known for their red tusks and black fur. They're similar to your average boars but are considerably stronger. Extra caution is advised when hunting these. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Akkala Highlands

12.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Mountain Goat --- **Description:** These herbivores make their home in meadows and rocky areas. Their characteristically strong legs and hooves facilitate easy climbing over rocks. Goats aren't very quick, so they make good targets for beginning hunters. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Meat --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, Great Hyrule Forest

13.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** White Goat --- **Description:** These goats are raised for their multiple uses. Their milk can be drank or made into butter, and their soft fur is used to make clothes. Domesticated goats wear bells around their necks so they can be easily found after being let out to graze. --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, Hyrule Ridge

14.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Mountain Buck --- **Description:** These male deer are usually found deep in the forest. They're well known for their huge, branching antlers, which they'll swing in self- defense if threatened. Deer are cautious by nature so it can be tricky getting close, but if you can capture one, you may be able to take it for a ride. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru, Hyrule Field

15.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Mountain Doe --- **Description:** These female deer are often found alongside a male. They're very timid animals by nature, but they tend to let their guard down when eating apples, a favorite food. This tidbit of information can be useful to hunters. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru, Hyrule Field

16.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Water Buffalo --- **Description:** These wild cows come equipped with big, strong horns. They live off grass that grows near the waterfront. Their meat is considered to be high quality, so they're a common target among hunters. Fun fact: the domesticated Hateno cow, often raised in villages, was bred through selective breeding using these. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Wetlands, Hyrule Ridge

17.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Hateno Cow --- **Description:** Originating in Hateno Village, these cows are kept as livestock primarily for their milk. Their horns are smaller than a water buffalo's, and they're much more docile and therefore easier to raise. Their horns are decorated with bright colors when taken out to pasture. --- **Common Locations:** Hateno Village, Lurelin Village

18.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Highland Sheep --- **Description:** Originally native to the mountainous regions, these sheep were domesticated for their wool and have since found a home in villages. Once the fluffy wool grows out, it's harvested and used to make clothing and bedding. They're calm, timid creatures and move about in small herds. --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, Akkala Highlands

19.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Grassland Fox --- **Description:** This breed of fox is common to grasslands and forests and is hallmarked by its fluffy, white-tipped tail. Unlike other foxes, they tend to act independently rather than form packs. Being omnivores, they hunt animals smaller than themselves and often stick to eating fruit and insects. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Lanayru Great Spring

20.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Snowcoat Fox --- **Description:** This particular breed of grassland fox makes its home in cold climates such as the Tabantha region. Its fur turned white as a means of adapting to snowy weather, serving as a natural camouflage. Because of this, spotting one in the snow takes a keen eye. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Tabantha Frontier

21.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Maraudo Wolf --- **Description:** These wolves are not only carnivorous but can also be downright fierce. They're highly aggressive and aren't afraid to attack people. They hunt in groups and surround their prey as a means of bringing it down. That said, if one of their own is injured, the rest are wise enough to run away. They communicate via howls, so if you're wandering the forest and hear their call, you had best take care. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Frontier, Eldin Canyon

22.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Wasteland Coyote --- **Description:** This contentious beast is native to the Gerudo region. It makes its home in the desert, so it doesn't have a problem with hot, arid climates. They do hunt other beasts and small animals but more often turn their sights on people. They're a threat to anyone traveling through the desert. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert, Gerudo Highlands

23.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Cold-Footed Wolf --- **Description:** This breed of maraudo wolf lives in snowy, mountainous areas, such as the Hebra Mountains. They travel in packs similar to their maraudo relatives but are considerably tougher thanks to having adapted to their harsh environment. They're made even more dangerous by their white fur, which provides a natural camouflage in the snow. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Gerudo Highlands

24.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Tabantha Moose --- **Description:** The largest breed of deer in Hyrule, this mammal's origin was traced back to the Tabantha region. It's easily distinguished by its immense antlers, which these moose shed and regrow yearly. Their meat is tender and high quality, so it works well in a stew. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Tundra, Hebra Mountains

25.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Dondon --- **Description:** A new species of four-legged beast found in southern regions. So far only five of these creatures have ever been spotted in Hyrule. Their diet is a mystery. But what is known is that they are easily scared, and their giant horns can be very dangerous. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

26.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Honeyvore Bear --- **Description:** This king among animals is dangerous game for even the most seasoned hunters. They'll attack anyone who wanders into their territory regardless of the wanderer's weaponry. As their name implies, they have a natural love of honey. Extreme caution is advised when you spot one, but if you're sneaky enough and maybe just a little bit crazy...you just may be able to ride one. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Courser Bee Honey, Raw Gourmet Meat --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, West Necluda

27.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Grizzlemaw Bear --- **Description:** This breed of honeyvore bear is distinguished by its gray fur. Even more ferocious than their relatives, they're commonly believed to be the most dangerous wild animal. They live in deep snow away from villages, so it's uncommon to encounter one. That said, if you do find one, you'd be better off not picking a fight with it. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Prime Meat, Raw Gourmet Meat, Hearty Salmon --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Gerudo Highlands

28.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Hylian Retriever --- **Description:** The native breed of this mammal varies by region, but one thing remains true: this animal has been known as "man's best friend" since ancient times. They're very clever and obedient, so aside from serving as pets, they are also put to work watching over grazing livestock. It's said that all Hylian retrievers are descendants of the dog once owned by the king of Hyrule. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Eldin Canyon

29.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Blupee --- **Description:** They may look like mere rabbits at a fleeting glance, but these strange and aptly named creatures glow with a mysterious blue light. While the details of their origins are entirely unknown, there is one thing we do know: these peculiar little things have a penchant for collecting rupees. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Unknown --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

30.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Bubbulfrog --- **Description:** These mysterious creatures dwell in caves all around the world. They like to stay hidden and will spew bubbles when threatened. When overcome, they disappear and leave behind mysterious objects. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Bubbul Gem --- **Common Locations:** Unknown

31.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Common Sparrow --- **Description:** As the name suggests, these birds are rather common around Hyrule. They mainly live in plains or forests but sometimes venture out to villages. Their diet consists of nuts and small insects. They look pretty cute when they jump around, but they don't have much love for people. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Lanayru Great Spring

32.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Red Sparrow --- **Description:** These small birds live in the Hebra region and eat mainly nuts and wild plants. Their bright- red feathers are often used as decorations. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Hyrule Ridge

33.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Blue Sparrow --- **Description:** This breed of sparrow is most often seen in the Lanayru region. They get most of their food from leaves and plants that grow near water. If it's safe enough, they can be spotted bathing in puddles or shallow rivers. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Great Spring, East Necluda

34.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Rainbow Sparrow --- **Description:** These small birds hail from the Faron region. As the name suggests, their feathers are more colorful than other sparrows', which has made them a favorite among dilettantes. They feed on small rain-forest insects, but the omnivore in them loves nuts as well. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Faron Grasslands, East Necluda

35.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Sand Sparrow --- **Description:** This desert-dwelling breed of sparrow has adapted to withstand the heat in the arid climate of the Gerudo region. Sometimes they can be spotted half-buried in the sand, holding perfectly still as a means of evading predators. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert

36.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Golden Sparrow --- **Description:** This breed of sparrow is native to the Eldin region. Their down is resistant to burning, an evolutionary trait produced by the harsh volcanic environment. They subsist on small insects that hide inside rocks. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Chickaloo Tree Nut --- **Common Locations:** Eldin Canyon, Great Sky Island

37.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Wood Pigeon --- **Description:** These pigeons inhabit vast regions all throughout Hyrule, so they can often be found in forests, grasslands, or even villages. They don't have a very strong sense of awareness, so even less-skilled hunters can nab them pretty easily. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Hyrule Ridge

38.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Rainbow Pigeon --- **Description:** This breed of pigeon is well known for its vivid feathers. They live mainly in the northern forests and grasslands of Hyrule. They're most fond of nuts and grain but won't pass up the occasional insect or earthworm if offered. Their meat is of a higher quality than a typical wood pigeon's. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Thigh --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Akkala Highlands

39.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Hotfeather Pigeon --- **Description:** This rare breed of pigeon lives near Death Mountain. Their fireproof feathers are valuable as clothing material. They usually prefer blazing-hot environments, but lately they've been spotted flying high in the sky where the air is cooler. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Thigh --- **Common Locations:** Eldin Sky Archipelago, Eldin Canyon

40.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** White Pigeon --- **Description:** This white-feathered breed of pigeon lives in the Hebra region. It's said that a wood pigeon survived atop a snowy mountain by changing its feathers to blend in with the snow and soon after became a white pigeon. They have an extra layer of fat to guard against the cold, so they have been known to yield high-quality meat. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Thigh, Raw Whole Bird --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Gerudo Highlands

41.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Accented Pigeon --- **Description:** The original variety of wood pigeon, these small birds once were seen all around Hyrule but are quite rare these days. Their color often serves as camouflage. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, East Gerudo Sky Archipelago

42.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Mountain Crow --- **Description:** This bird is known for its cleverness and for its distinct claws. They make their homes in mountains, forests, and villages alike. Not only are their jet-black feathers seen as an ill omen, but they'll steal the crops right out of a farmer's hands if given the chance. Because of this, they're often met with enmity. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Great Hyrule Forest, Hyrule Ridge

43.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Bright-Chested Duck --- **Description:** These birds can be found on waterfronts all over Hyrule. Their webbed feet make them excellent swimmers, and their long necks allow them to duck their heads underwater to find food. Their fatty meat is high quality. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Lanayru Wetlands

44.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Blue-Winged Heron --- **Description:** These birds live on waterfronts all throughout Hyrule. Their characteristically thin legs and long necks help them catch water-dwelling fish or frogs for food. They lie perfectly still in wait for their prey and then stretch out their long necks to capture their meal. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, Lanayru Wetlands

45.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Pink Heron --- **Description:** This breed of heron is characterized by the pink tips of its feathers. Unlike its waterfront- dwelling relative the blue-winged heron, these live in grasslands or arid regions and subsist on insects that live in the grass. They can often be found walking about searching for food but will fly away if they sense danger. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Central Hyrule Sky

46.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Islander Hawk --- **Description:** These carnivorous birds live in plains or highlands. They use their sharp talons and beaks to catch and eat small animals and other birds. They soar calmly through the sky and search for prey from above. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Thigh --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Gerudo Canyon

47.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Seagull --- **Description:** These birds live near the ocean. They eat mainly fish, so a flock of seagulls hovering over water is a good indication of where there are fish. Fishermen use this to their advantage when searching for a catch of their own. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Necluda Sea, Lanayru Sea

48.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Cloud Seagull --- **Description:** This seagull subspecies dwells mostly at high altitudes and is rarely seen on the surface, although one can occasionally be glimpsed through the clouds. They excel at catching updrafts and gliding around the sky, rarely flapping their wings. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Drumstick --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, North Necluda Sky Archipelago

49.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Eldin Ostrich --- **Description:** This large bird makes its home in the volcanic region of Eldin. Their heat-resistant feathers and skin are evolutionary traits produced by the harsh environment. Their wings are too small to facilitate flight, but their long legs make them pretty speedy runners. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Bird Thigh, Raw Whole Bird --- **Common Locations:** Death Mountain, Eldin Mountains

50.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Forest Ostrich --- **Description:** Flightless birds that are thought to have roamed all over Hyrule back when it had more grasslands. They resist cold but don't do well in hot climates because of their thick body covering. They're very alert and often turn their attention from the grass to look around. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Raw Meat --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, South Lanayru Sky Archipelago

51.content: --- **Category:** creatures --- **Name:** Cucco --- **Description:** Villages often raise these birds for their eggs, but some people actually keep them as pets. They can't fly but can flap their wings mighty furiously if picked up. They're usually calm creatures, but if you're persistent in your torment of them... Well... --- **Recoverable Materials:** Bird Egg --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, West Necluda

52.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Hyrule Bass --- **Description:** An ordinary fish that hasn't changed for ages. It can be eaten raw, but cooking it amplifies its healing benefits. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, West Necluda --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered

53.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Hearty Bass --- **Description:** This large fish lives near the water's edge. Its sizable body can store a lot of nutrients. When used in cooking, it'll restore all your hearts and increase your maximum hearts. --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Sky Archipelago, West Hebra Sky Archipelago --- **Hearts Recovered:** 2.0 hearts recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Extra Hearts

54.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Staminoka Bass --- **Description:** This Hyrule bass got to be the biggest fish by never getting caught (until now). Its long life results in a cooked dish that will restore a lot of stamina. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, West Necluda --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Stamina Recovery

55.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Hearty Salmon --- **Description:** This fish makes its home in cold water, giving it extra layers of fat. It'll restore all your hearts and temporarily increase your maximum hearts when used in cooking. --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Tabantha Frontier --- **Hearts Recovered:** 4.0 hearts recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Extra Hearts

56.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Chillfin Trout --- **Description:** This blue trout prefers cold bodies of water. Its skin contains enzymes that keep its body cool, and when cooked into a dish, it will temporarily boost your heat resistance. --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Lanayru Great Spring --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Heat Resistance

57.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Sizzlefin Trout --- **Description:** This red trout prefers warm bodies of water. It has a special organ specifically for storing heat. When cooked into a dish, it temporarily boosts your resistance to the cold. --- **Common Locations:** Eldin Canyon, Hebra Mountains --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Cold Resistance

58.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Voltfin Trout --- **Description:** This trout makes its home in the freshwater lakes. Its scales have an insulating compound that, when cooked into a dish, offers resistance to electricity. --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Frontier --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Shock Resistance

59.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Stealthfin Trout --- **Description:** Consuming the bioluminescent compound that makes this fish glow in the dark will increase concentration. Dishes cooked with it will suppress noise when consumed. --- **Common Locations:** Great Hyrule Forest --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Stealth Up

60.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Mighty Carp --- **Description:** This freshwater fish lives alongside its less mighty carp ilk. A compound in its liver promotes muscle growth. Dishes cooked with it will temporarily increase your attack power. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Great Spring, Akkala Highlands --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Attack Up

61.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Armored Carp --- **Description:** Calcium deposits in the scales of this ancient fish make them as hard as armor. Cooking it into a dish will fortify your bones, temporarily increasing your defense. --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, Lanayru Great Spring --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Defense Up

62.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Sanke Carp --- **Description:** This wild armored carp has been bred into a prizewinning fish. Its beautifully colored markings do not occur in nature. It offers no special effects when cooked. --- **Common Locations:** Kakariko Village --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered

63.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Ancient Arowana --- **Description:** A lively fish that hasn't changed much since ancient times. Its nutritious meat can restore a bit of health. --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, North Tabantha Sky Archipelago --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered

64.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Glowing Cave Fish --- **Description:** A luminous fish that lives in dark caves. When consumed, its light enzyme can make one's body glow. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Caves --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Glow

65.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Mighty Porgy --- **Description:** This ocean-dwelling fish comes with one rude attitude. The compounds in its flesh elevate your competitive spirit when it's cooked into a dish, thus increasing your attack power. --- **Common Locations:** Faron Sea, Necluda Sea --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Attack Up

66.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Armored Porgy --- **Description:** This porgy's body is covered in armor-hard scales. The compounds in its scales, when cooked into a dish, fortify your bones and temporarily boost your defense. --- **Common Locations:** Necluda Sea, Lanayru Sea --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Defense Up

67.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Sneaky River Snail --- **Description:** This large, glow-in-the-dark snail lives in fresh water. When cooked into a dish, it heightens your senses so you can move about silently. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Ridge, Zora's Domain --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Stealth Up

68.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Razorclaw Crab --- **Description:** This crab is well known for its exceptionally sharp pincers. When cooked, the strength compound in its claws will increase your attack power. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Sea, Necluda Sea --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Attack Up

69.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Ironshell Crab --- **Description:** This crab's shell is particularly hard. When cooked into a dish, its fat and meat bolster the body to increase your defense. --- **Common Locations:** Necluda Sea, Faron Sea --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Defense Up

70.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Bright-Eyed Crab --- **Description:** This crab appears in large numbers when it rains. One bite of its delectable meat, and you'll forget all your exhaustion. Replenishes your stamina when cooked into a dish. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Wetlands, Lanayru Great Spring --- **Hearts Recovered:** 1.0 heart recovered --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Stamina Recovery

71.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Fairy --- **Description:** This fairy will fly from your pouch and heal you the moment you lose your last heart. It's easily mistaken for a firefly at first, but it glows in the daylight as well as night. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Caves, Hyrule Sky Islands --- **Hearts Recovered:** 5.0 hearts recovered

72.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Winterwing Butterfly --- **Description:** The powdery scales of this butterfly's wings cool the air near it. Watching it flutter around snowflakes is a thing of beauty. Cook it with monster parts for a heat-resistance elixir. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Highlands, Mount Lanayru --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Heat Resistance

73.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Summerwing Butterfly --- **Description:** A butterfly found in the woods and plains of warm regions. Its wings absorb the warmth of the sun. Cook it with monster parts to create an elixir that makes you feel warm and fuzzy. --- **Common Locations:** Eldin Canyon, Gerudo Highlands --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Cold Resistance

74.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Thunderwing Butterfly --- **Description:** This rare butterfly only shows itself when it rains. The organs in its body produce an insulating compound. When made into an elixir, it offers electrical resistance. --- **Common Locations:** Thunderhead Isles, Faron Grasslands --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Shock Resistance

75.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Smotherwing Butterfly --- **Description:** This rare butterfly lives in volcanic regions. Its body contains a heat-resistant liquid, which can be turned into a topical elixir that offers resistance to flames. --- **Common Locations:** Death Mountain, Eldin Canyon --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Flame Guard

76.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Cold Darner --- **Description:** This dragonfly prefers the cool shade of trees to the warmth of the sun. Its wings disperse heat from its body, which can be cooked into a heat-resistance elixir. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Highlands, Mount Lanayru --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Heat Resistance

77.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Warm Darner --- **Description:** This dragonfly has a special organ that causes it to sweat profusely. Cook it with monster parts for an elixir that will raise your core temperature so you can resist the cold. --- **Common Locations:** Akkala Highlands, Faron Grasslands --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Cold Resistance

78.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Electric Darner --- **Description:** This rare dragonfly only appears in the rain. Its wings direct electricity away from its body. Cook it with monster parts for an electricity- resistance elixir. --- **Common Locations:** Thunderhead Isles, West Necluda --- **Hearts Recovered:** No restorative effect --- **Unique Cooking Effects:** Shock Resistance

79.content: --- **Category:** critters --- **Name:** Restless Cricket --- **Description:** A very energetic cricket. Ideal for taking down quick-moving targets. --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, Deep Akkala --- **Properties:** - Bow - 10x3 Attack

352.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Mighty Lynel Bow --- **Description:** This massive Lynel bow sports a bowstring made from a metal so tough, mere Hylians have trouble drawing it back. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Great Spring, Akkala Highlands Depths --- **Properties:** - Bow - 20x3 Attack

353.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Savage Lynel Bow --- **Description:** This Lynel bow is made from a special steel found at the peak of Death Mountain. It has tremendous stopping power and can pierce thick armor as easily as thin paper. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Highlands, Lanayru Wetlands Depths --- **Properties:** - Bow - 32x3 Attack

354.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Duplex Bow --- **Description:** A bow favored by the skilled archers of the Yiga Clan. It's been engineered to fire two arrows at once to ensure your target comes to a swift and none-too-pleasant halt. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Gerudo Desert Depths --- **Properties:** - Bow - 14x2 Attack

355.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Construct Bow --- **Description:** A bow used by a Captain Construct. Though simply built, it is made of fireproof materials and won't catch fire as wooden bows do. --- **Common Locations:** South Lanayru Sky Archipelago, North Gerudo Sky Archipelago --- **Properties:** - Bow - 5 Attack

356.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Strong Construct Bow --- **Description:** A sturdy bow for a Captain Construct. Besides being fireproof, it's been strengthened to allow for more powerful shots. --- **Common Locations:** Rising Island Chain, Death Mountain Depths --- **Properties:** - Bow - 11 Attack

357.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Mighty Construct Bow --- **Description:** A powerful bow for a Captain Construct. Though still fireproof, it's more complex than earlier models. The bowstring is extremely tense and requires great strength to draw. --- **Common Locations:** Lomei Labyrinth Island, Thyphlo Ruins --- **Properties:** - Bow - 24 Attack

358.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Zonaite Bow --- **Description:** A Zonai bow that draws power from your Energy Cell. Power drains, and arrows can fly much farther according to how long a shot is charged. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Bow - 30 Attack

359.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Demon King's Bow --- **Description:** A magical bow prized by the Demon King. Its performance reflects the power of its wielder. The higher your maximum number of hearts, the more its attack power increases. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Bow - 2-60 Attack

360.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Hylian Shield --- **Description:** A shield passed down through the Hyrulean royal family, along with the legend of the hero who wielded it. Its defensive capabilities and durability outshine all other shields. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Shield Guard

361.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Pot Lid --- **Description:** The lid of a large soup pot. It smells vaguely of poultry broth... Yum! It can take quite a beating before breaking. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, East Necluda --- **Properties:** - Shield - 1 Shield Guard

362.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Old Wooden Shield --- **Description:** An aged, worn-out wooden shield. It can withstand lighter attacks, such as arrows. --- **Common Locations:** Great Sky Island, Gerudo Desert --- **Properties:** - Shield - 2 Shield Guard

363.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Wooden Shield --- **Description:** This lightweight, simple shield is ideal for less experienced fighters. It can withstand light attacks, but blocking stronger blows is not recommended. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Hebra Mountains --- **Properties:** - Shield - 2 Shield Guard

364.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Emblazoned Shield --- **Description:** This shield features a traditional design from Necluda. Its combat capabilities aren't much better than the standard wooden shield, but it found popularity for its design. --- **Common Locations:** West Necluda, East Necluda --- **Properties:** - Shield - 3 Shield Guard

365.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Hunter's Shield --- **Description:** Favored by hunters for its rabbit design, which is said to bring luck on hunts. It's easy to use, but its durability leaves something to be desired. --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Frontier, Hebra Mountains --- **Properties:** - Shield - 3 Shield Guard

366.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Fisherman's Shield --- **Description:** Often carried by fishermen for its fish design, which represents hope for a great catch. Its light wooden construction makes it convenient to take onto a boat. --- **Common Locations:** Lurelin Village --- **Properties:** - Shield - 3 Shield Guard

367.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Traveler's Shield --- **Description:** A sturdy shield loved by many an adventurer. It is made of animal hide and sturdy wood and is best suited to defending against weak monsters or animals. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Eldin Mountains --- **Properties:** - Shield - 4 Shield Guard

368.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Soldier's Shield --- **Description:** A shield once used by the guards of Hyrule Castle. It's easy to handle, but its core is made of wood, so it can catch fire. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Eldin Canyon --- **Properties:** - Shield - 16 Shield Guard

369.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Knight's Shield --- **Description:** A shield favored by the knights who served the Hyrulean royal family. Its sturdy metal construction makes it quite durable, but its weight requires decent skill to wield. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert, Tabantha Frontier Depths --- **Properties:** - Shield - 40 Shield Guard

370.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Royal Shield --- **Description:** A shield issued to the Hyrulean royal family's immediate guard detail. It boasts a high defense, but these days it's more a collector's item due to its ornamentation. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Gerudo Highlands Depths --- **Properties:** - Shield - 55 Shield Guard

371.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Forest Dweller's Shield --- **Description:** The Koroks made this shield specifically for Hylians. It's made from the finest hard wood of trees that grow only in Korok Forest, so it's sturdier than it looks. --- **Common Locations:** Great Hyrule Forest --- **Properties:** - Shield - 30 Shield Guard

372.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Zora Shield --- **Description:** A Zora-made shield adorned with intricate ornamentation. It's said that true masters of this shield can redirect attacks as a rock redirects rushing water. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Great Spring, Lanayru Great Spring Sky --- **Properties:** - Shield - 24 Shield Guard

373.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Kite Shield --- **Description:** Rito warriors cherish this shield. Its unique shape is designed with midbattle flight in mind to facilitate aerial combat. --- **Common Locations:** Hebra Mountains, Tabantha Frontier --- **Properties:** - Shield - 14 Shield Guard

374.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Gerudo Shield --- **Description:** The design of this metal shield has changed over time to match the Gerudo's sword-and- shield fighting style. It's favored by soldiers and travelers alike. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert, Gerudo Highlands --- **Properties:** - Shield - 28 Shield Guard

375.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Radiant Shield --- **Description:** This extravagant shield is presented to Gerudo warriors who rise to the rank of captain. Its apparent opulence is rivaled only by its combat capabilities. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert, Gerudo Highlands --- **Properties:** - Shield - 35 Shield Guard

376.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Daybreaker --- **Description:** This shield was cherished by the Gerudo Champion Urbosa. The gold used to make it was handpicked to ensure a design that is both lightweight and very durable. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Town --- **Properties:** - Shield - 48 Shield Guard

377.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Shield of the Mind's Eye --- **Description:** A small Sheikah-made shield. Its design is intended to decrease blind spots without sacrificing too much defense. --- **Common Locations:** East Necluda, West Necluda --- **Properties:** - Shield - 16 Shield Guard

378.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Sea-Breeze Shield --- **Description:** A shield said to have been the favorite of a hero who traveled the open seas. It was apparently a family heirloom, passed down through many generations. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Shield - 65 Shield Guard

379.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Rusty Shield --- **Description:** It's likely this rusty old shield once belonged to a knight. It still has some defensive capabilities, but its usefulness has been worn down by time. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, East Necluda --- **Properties:** - Shield - 3 Shield Guard

380.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Royal Guard's Shield --- **Description:** This shield was forged using ancient Sheikah technology. It boasts extremely high stopping power, but its structural weakness made its low durability impractical for combat. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Shield - 70 Shield Guard

381.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Boko Shield --- **Description:** A Bokoblin-made shield created by attaching a handhold to any flat tree bark picked up off the ground. It's pretty shoddy, so don't expect it to last very long. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Hebra Mountains --- **Properties:** - Shield - 3 Shield Guard

382.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Spiked Boko Shield --- **Description:** A Boko shield made of slightly stronger wood and reinforced with animal bones. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, East Necluda --- **Properties:** - Shield - 10 Shield Guard

383.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Dragonbone Boko Shield --- **Description:** This Boko shield is reinforced with fossilized bone. Its defensive capabilities are respectable, but its predictably slipshod craftsmanship spells low durability. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Highlands, Gerudo Desert --- **Properties:** - Shield - 25 Shield Guard

384.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Lizal Shield --- **Description:** A common shield found among the Lizalfos. It's made of metal, but its sloppy craftsmanship offers poor durability. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Great Spring, Faron Sea --- **Properties:** - Shield - 15 Shield Guard

385.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Reinforced Lizal Shield --- **Description:** This Lizal shield has been strengthened by adding a different type of metal to the mix. The edge is lined with spikes, so handle with care. --- **Common Locations:** Tabantha Tundra, Abandoned Kakariko Mine --- **Properties:** - Shield - 22 Shield Guard

386.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Steel Lizal Shield --- **Description:** This Lizal shield is adorned with several metal shells as a means of reinforcement. Its defensive capabilities are high, but its weight requires a skilled soldier to bear. --- **Common Locations:** Gerudo Desert, Mount Lanayru --- **Properties:** - Shield - 36 Shield Guard

387.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Zonaite Shield --- **Description:** A shield used by Zonai and made of zonaite. It lowers the energy consumption of an attached Zonai device. --- **Common Locations:** Necluda Sky Archipelago, Eldin Sky Archipelago --- **Properties:** - Shield - 11 Shield Guard

388.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Strong Zonaite Shield --- **Description:** A shield used by Zonai and made of zonaite. It is moderately durable and lowers the energy consumption of an attached Zonai device. --- **Common Locations:** Lanayru Sky Archipelago, Lomei Labyrinth Island --- **Properties:** - Shield - 26 Shield Guard

389.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Mighty Zonaite Shield --- **Description:** A shield used by Zonai and made of zonaite. It is very durable and draws on its stored energy to more efficiently use an attached Zonai device. --- **Common Locations:** Unknown --- **Properties:** - Shield - 50 Shield Guard

390.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Lynel Shield --- **Description:** A sturdy shield favored by Lynels for its defensive and offensive capabilities. First and foremost a shield, but the bladed edges can deal slashing attacks when deflecting. --- **Common Locations:** Hyrule Field, Central Hyrule Depths --- **Properties:** - Shield - 30 Shield Guard

391.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Mighty Lynel Shield --- **Description:** This Lynel-made shield has been reinforced with armor and even more blades. Stronger in both defense and offense, it can tear through basic armor when deflecting. --- **Common Locations:** Faron Grasslands, Eldin Canyon Depths --- **Properties:** - Shield - 44 Shield Guard

392.content: --- **Category:** equipment --- **Name:** Savage Lynel Shield --- **Description:** This ultimate Lynel shield is favored by the White-Maned Lynels. It excels at defending against even the most brutal of attacks and cutting down powerful foes when deflecting. --- **Common Locations:** Akkala Highlands, Central Hyrule Depths --- **Properties:** - Shield - 62 Shield Guard

393.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Treasure Chest --- **Description:** Fortunes untold (potentially) await the lucky adventurer who finds one of these. Chests can often be found within shrines or at enemy camps, but there may be some crafty folks who think they're safer underground. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Treasures --- **Common Locations:** Greater Hyrule

394.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Ore Deposit --- **Description:** This deposit contains a good deal of ore. Breaking the rock will yield rock salt, flint, and other ore and minerals of varying value. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Diamond, Ruby, Sapphire, Topaz, Opal, Amber, Rock Salt, Flint --- **Common Locations:** Greater Hyrule

395.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Rare Ore Deposit --- **Description:** This deposit contains a good deal of precious ore and the occasional rare mineral, like ruby and sapphire. Break it open to see what it has to offer! --- **Recoverable Materials:** Diamond, Ruby, Sapphire, Topaz, Amber, Flint --- **Common Locations:** Greater Hyrule

396.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Luminous Stone Deposit --- **Description:** This deposit contains quite a bit of luminous stone. Crack it open to get at the easily processed rocks within. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Luminous Stone, Flint --- **Common Locations:** Greater Hyrule

397.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Zonaite Deposit --- **Description:** This deposit glows with mysterious energy and is very common in the Depths. If you crack it open, you can claim the zonaite within. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Zonaite, Large Zonaite --- **Common Locations:** The Depths

398.content: --- **Category:** treasures --- **Name:** Well --- **Description:** A hole dug in the earth to draw water from underground. Can be found in stables, towns, and sometimes even ruins. Home to a variety of unique fauna and flora. --- **Recoverable Materials:** Materials --- **Common Locations:** Greater Hyrule
